I asked him how they going to correct this once again he doesn't know. Ask to speak with with a manager after being hold again, Josh said no available. I said I need to contact corporate this isn't helping. This company has bad customer service I wouldn't get any card from this company. I asked Josh what am I supposed to tell the retailer because he didn't give me any real information.

Once I payoff my balance I will be canceling my card Upgrade. They will not contact you if their is problem. Bad customer service. It's humiliating that I have to contact this retailer about my transaction being declined even though I have the funds available.</Review>

< review>
I didn't like the high interest on my credit cards...23.99%, 22.99%, and 20.99. I took out a loan at Upgrade that would let me pay down my credit cards so my monthly minimum payment on each is now only $25.00. I do have a monthly payment now for the loan but their APR is at 13.55% which will save me quite a bit of money. Additionally there is no prepayment clause. I will be able to pay more than the minimum and that will also save me money. The online application process is easy to complete. I filled out the application on a Saturday and the money was deposited in my bank on Monday. And, best of all, my credit cards will be nearly paid off by Tuesday! Highly recommend.</review>

< Text>
I waited too long to try this spot!

And food trucks feel like the perfect pandemic solution right now!!

I order the falafel over rice and my husband orders the lamb!

The falafel is so tasty! We both order spicy!! Who'd have thought lettuce would taste so good with rice ? Those sauces are amazing and the textures mix so well

As for the lamb my husband found it super tender and tasty to eat!

The portions are also incredibly generous, I had it for lunch and dinner!

I can't imagine there's many places that you can get a full meal including a drink for $10

The service is friendly and fast ! Overall the perfect spot to grab lunch on the go / near campus</Text>

< Review>
As a mechanical engineer, Shah's was the go-to lunch since it was next to Bainer. It was and still is the best halal food I've had. Great taste and perfect portion size. If you're new to Davis, student or not, stop by this place. Super delicious food and employees are super nice.</Review>

<Rating>5< /Rating>< text>
Hands down my favorite spot to eat in the Sacramento area. I crave it often and frequently make the 30 minute drive to get it. I usually order half chicken half lamb over rice (spicy) with pita bread. They take credit cards now which is convenient, and the guys running it are great. I just wish there were more locations, specifically in Sacramento. Everyone should know the deliciousness of Shah's Halal Food. Such a gem.<//text>

Follow-up #5: It's like a Disney movie - a happy ending and all. One of the original orders that hadn't been sent was refunded even though I had confirmed I still wanted the products. They apologized and said they would get the order out to me, and at no charge! Much better CS since the beginning, which is why I am now giving them a 4-star rating.

Follow-up #4: Changed to 3-star rating. 2 of the 3 orders finally arrived!! It took forever, but worth the wait since the products are good. I checked on the 3rd order. Their response a couple days later was covid-related issues. It would have been nice if 1) they had informed me of this when the order was first placed, and 2) they could give me a shipping date. Oh well.

Because of finally receiving the orders, and because I like the products and the company story, I will change my star rating to 3 stars. IF and when they change up their CS and supply chain process, I'll re-rate them again.

Follow-up #3: I was ready to change my rating back to four stars, but it seems the saga continues. Reading through the other one star reviews, I noticed that someone from JB suggested the person contact the company directly via a different email address, one that is not posted on their site. So, I decided to try this approach. Lo and behold, I FINALLY reached the right person! I briefly explained my situation, and, although at first they didn't respond to my email directly, within ten minutes I received alerts that all three orders had been processed! I also received separate alerts with tracking numbers. A total miracle!!! But I then checked the tracking and all it said was that labels were created and that my orders had been assigned tracking - nothing had been shipped. ARGH! Once again, a total letdown. Their customer service person finally responded to one of my multiple emails and said that because of COVID, employees had to stay 6' apart from one another, which is why the orders hadn't been shipped. This makes no sense. And, it's also no excuse for poor communication with customers since it's all through email. Hopefully I'll get my orders soon. I still love their products.

Follow-up #2: I have continued to contact customer service again (twice) and still no response whatsoever from anyone. No orders delivered. Nothing! I do keep receiving email promotions though, so it seems they're still in business.

Follow-up: After numerous emails asking about my cancelled order, their reply was "Thank you for your email. You will receive a new tracking number on Monday. The shipping label was created and then cancelled. We apologize for the inconvenience." NO reasoning whatsoever. NO attempt to compensate for their incompetencies. This is beyond frustrating and disappointing.

The products are great, but absolute worst customer service of any company I've ever had to deal with! I have placed three orders over the past two and a half weeks and haven't received one item. After contacting CS 6 times, someone finally responded to my email saying that orders take 7 - 10 business days. They finally processed one order but when I went to check the tracking number, the screen prompt on the Fed Ex site said the seller had cancelled the order. I contacted JB again but still never hear from anyone. What the heck? If another company comes up with products that match JB, then I'll switch. For now, I'm giving them a one star review - I will update this based on the outcome.<//review>

Julian Bakery is mostly an on-line seller of keto/paleo food products.  On an application such as Google Maps, the only ‚Äúrating‚Äù should be a visit to this particular location AND NOT JUST ITS MAIL ORDER PRODUCTS.  Example:  The Tillamook Cheese factory in Tillamook, Oregon is a tourist attraction with a factory tour and lots of cheese shopping.  When you go to Tillamook, you are rating the visit and not merely its cheese.  That is, Tillamook could have great cheese but it‚Äôs a lousy tourist visit, or vice-versa (I liked both aspects, for the record).  In the case of Julian Bakery, I can‚Äôt tell if anyone has actually visited this location...if there‚Äôs a tour with product samples, etc.  If you want to rate its products you buy from Amazon, then USE AMAZON TO RATE ITS PRODUCTS. < review>
I don't understand the poor ratings here.
I will agree that shipping is slow but I found that their customer service was more than helpful.
I ordered the variety 3 pack that contained the almond, seed medley and coconut bread.  All three are very good and are solid alternatives to traditional bread if you have gluten issues or are trying to reduce your grain/carb and/or calorie intake.  I especially like the seed medley toasted with avocado or as a sandwich.
You must freeze these products immediately and keep them in the freezer until ready to use because they contain no preservatives.
If you are looking for something exactly like bread, you might be disappointed but this is the best no grain bread I have ever eaten and I will continue to order from Julian Bakery.<//review>

< text>
I felt strongly to write about my experience.   About three months ago I ordered the bread and I had unexpected travel so I wrote to the company asking to refund my order and they gave me my money back immediately as it had not shipped. I was excited to try again and was a bit bummed reading all these reviews.   Clearly, Julian Bakery has worked really hard to improve their distribution which seemed to be the cause of the issues of a lot of their poor reviews (mold etc).   I received my keto bread 2 days via FedEx after it shipped.   Now if you are not accustomed to keto or you have never made your own true keto bread, you maybe caught off guard as it is not like traditional bread.  YES it is more moist almost cake like but hello....it's keto and that's the point due to the high fat content.   I carefully inspected the 3 packages and they were totally fine.  Yes the bread slightly smells but that is due to no preservatives and the cream cheese.  It toasted perfectly on a longer setting as keto bread will take longer to toast.  I actually had the best experience, found the bread to be delicious and it tasted exactly like my own when I bake it.   This is a lifesaver as I can save time now!   My only request would be for organic unblanced almond flour.   Absolutely I would order again!!!< /text>

I really don't understand the barrage of negative comments here. Yes, there is a delay in shipping but you will get your most definitely. I ordered 4-5 times from this company and got my bars every single time.

The taste varies, some are bad but the good ones are excellent. My favorite is chocolate devil's food cake. Second one is the Vanilla pudding.

These bars will fill you up and curb your appetite. I have zero bloating after eating them and I have a sensitive GI system.

Eat them when they are warm, they are tastier when they are chewy.

Their Ketone body product is not better than its counterparts from Pruvet but it is literally half the price. I really recommend the bars and they are getting much better with their wait time.< /Text>

<resp>None< /resp>< Review>
This is the review that I have posted on Yelp.  Evidently the owners never respond to those reviews, so I will post it here.  In addition, I guess I am an idiot, because when I called regarding my last order (placed 3/22 and still not received as of today 4/26) the girl assured me that it was a Paleo bar problem and if I had ordered the primal bars they were shipping out immediately.  So like an idiot, I ordered the primal bars on 4/18 and still no bars! and of course, no response..... I love these bars, and it is horrible that they cannot work out the shipping issues.

YELP REVIEW:
This is going to be a mixed review because I absolutely LOVE their Paleo bars.  I am not a big fan of the flavors that I originally thought might be my favorite, mint & cookies and cream, but they are still ok.  I have ordered the variety packs to get each flavor.  My favorite are glazed donut, cinnamon roll, coconut shred, and  caramel.  If you have tried low sugar/high protein products you will appreciate the great taste and wonderful texture of these bars.  If you are new to the low sugar/high protein market, I could understand how it might not be what you were expecting, For medical reasons, I had to drastically reduce my sugar intake, while also increasing my fiber and protein.  I have tried many many products and this one has become a staple for me.  I was so happy to find something that satisfies a sweet craving while providing lots of protein and fiber both.  That being said about the wonderful product....

The shipping is a joke.  I have a few other products I would love to try but they can't seem to get the bugs worked out on their shipping issues.  I live in the country (way out) and USPS is the worst possible way to receive deliveries.  I am into my third order  placed on 2/3/16 (each order having it's own shipping issues).  On this order, 2/5 I received a confirmation, and on 2/8 I received a tracking number that my package would be shipped 2nd day USPS on 2/10. On 2/10 I received another email stating it had left and should arrive to me by 2/12.  The tracking number that they provided still hasn't left the store as of today 2/16/16.  I sent 2 emails asking for updates with no response.  So I called today and the girl answering the phone, Katie, said that they had encountered some problems in production and my shipment had not left yet.  I am absolutely not upset at all that something has come up in production.  I am upset that no one would answer my emails about food getting lost in our postal service for 6 days.  Communication makes all the difference in the world.  If their shipping information was dependable, I would absolutely rate them a 5 star business.  I sure hope they work this out (UPS and Fed Ex are much more reliable).

I am a huge fan of their product and was excited about trying more items, but it doesn't do any good to make a good product that you can't get delivered.<//Review>

< rating>
3</rating>
<Review>Good product, terrible logistics and service.

First, the good: I think the Paleo bars are actually quite good. Note that they use Stevia and not sugar... so they do have the aftertaste usually associated with alternative sweeteners. Thankfully it doesn't bother me, so I quite enjoy the bars. I'd say the cinnamon roll ones are my favorite. These have helped me curb my sugar addiction, for sure!

The OK: Some of the bars are a little oily, as others stated, but whatever. They are soft and chewy kind of like the big sticks of tootsie rolls. Most of the bars use egg protein which sits with me better than whey. But, with a lot of high-protein, high-fiber foods (at least in my experience), they can cause cramps. Again, I've not been affected by this - but a friend who tried a bar from the same batch I was eating said they got cramps. I guess it varies from person to person.

The bad: Their shipping is an absolute joke. Three orders, and it's always the same. Wait two weeks for the shipping notification and tracking number. (Two day shipping, right?) Then, another week or two from getting the tracking number to when they actually bother to ship it. *Then* it actually comes in 2-3 days. It's 4-5 week minimum wait from when you order.

And you know what? I'd be OK with that if they were just up front about this. I've never actually gotten a hold of any customer service rep (I did try emailing the "sales" address, to no avail). But from the excuses I've seen: swamped with orders, machine malfunction, whatever, it sounds like it wouldn't matter. Unless they have a machine breaking down every time I order, they're just not being honest with themselves about their real turnaround time. FINE. Just be up front on the site that it takes a while... and don't tease me with a tracking number which is useless for another week (or two).

I'm currently waiting on what will probably be my last order. It's a shame, really... Just a little more transparency and messaging and everything would be fine, and this would be a 5 star review. But seeing the same complaints (and responses) going back for years, it seems like they just don't get it. Too bad.< /Review>< resp>

<Resp>None</Resp><gmapID>0x80dc71b8970d464d:0xd3469738c74cf5a7<//gmapID><user_name>E B<//user_name>< review>
If I could give zero stars, I would.

This is entirely regarding their online business and has no bearing on their brick and mortar, which I have never visited, but if you're considering ordering online from them, RUN - DON'T WALK - to literally any other supplier.  I placed an order back at the end of March.  I was told it would ship in early April.  I was sent a tracking number and told that I would receive my product by April 8th.

April 11th rolled around and the shipping status was still "pending," so I emailed them.  No response.  I emailed a second time.  No response.  (AND YES, I CHECKED MY SPAM FILTERS, THANK YOU.  Nothing in spam, either.) Thank God I went through PayPal, because I then opened a ticket with them.  Three times I attempted to contact them through PayPal's system, and sure enough - no response.  I escalated to PayPal, which gave them 10 days to respond to PayPal itself, and - you guessed it - NO RESPONSE.  I was just issued my refund through PayPal because the bakery never even replied.

I don't know what their deal is, but their online sales practices are extremely shady.  Not worth it, but if you absolutely MUST try, use your PayPal account - DO NOT give them your credit card information, because if they can't even reply to PayPal, the probability of you getting a refund should you fail to receive your product is likely null unless you have PayPal's arbitration to back you up.

I'll likely be filing a few reports regarding this company, because I'm not sure if they realize this, but their business practices are seriously toeing the "fraudulent" line (and that's being generous, since I'm pretty sure, based on other complaints on here, that they've long since fully jumped over that line).  I can't emphasize this enough - DO NOT ORDER ONLINE FROM THEM.</review>

< Review>
TLDR: Impressively incompetent, dirty, and scammy. Do not waste your time, money, or teeth. Also, there are ants.

I had to give them my insurance information four times before it stuck. Two of these times they called me at work. I was in for a simple cleaning. It took over two hours, in large part because they didn't call me until about 40 minutes after my appointment has supposed to start. I just started a new job and left early for this appointment, so this made me really angry. Complete indifference when I asked what was going on.

A hygienist started polishing my teeth, stopped because she said the machine wasn't working (which made sense given that the paste was all over my face, my hair, my arms, and my pants) and then left without rinsing out my mouth. A few minutes later another woman came over to tell me that it would be another ten minutes because someone was on break. When a woman did come over to finish the polishing (using the "broken" machine) she wasn't even wearing her face mask properly and kept shoving the vacuum down my throat. Note that that was just the polishing, it took another two people to finish the cleaning.

The dentist did not bother to introduce himself and spent maybe a minute with me. He then recommended some procedures, one of which I had never heard of and was not covered by my insurance. When I asked the hygienist what the benefits were, the only thing she could tell me that was it, "makes your gums feel cleaner." Yeah, I am not about to pay $360 out of pocket to make my gums feel cleaner if that's the only reason to do it.

After the appointment I was contacted saying I owed $144 for opening an account with Western Dental. I had no idea what they were talking about. I called the dentist office and they were charging me $94 for fillings I had not had done and $50 for X-rays which they had previously said the insurance was covering. I asked multiple times before I left if I owed anything and they had said that everything was covered. I've checked with my insurance and the X-rays are covered, so I have no idea what their problem is.

Oh yes, and they have ants. Everywhere.

To sum up: they are inconsiderate, incompetent, and rude, they will try very hard to suck your wallet dry, and the place is filthy with I do not want to know what and ants.< /Review>

Now you might be thinking, what‚Äôs a Hong Kong Style Bakery; this genre is nothing ground breaking but having grown up on this stuff, there are some definite classics: 1) Hong Kong Style Milk Tea, 2) cocktail bun, 3) red bean bun, 4) Taro bun, 5) egg tarts, 6) HK style Swiss roll.  I think they do a great job with these items.  I tried the chicken pie which they also made well.  It brought back a lot memories with some buttery goodness.

Doug Spindler<//username>
<Date>1582496492681</Date><rate>5</rate><text>Can't believe the dummies who give it a 1, 2 or 3 star reviews with comments like it's just a gate as in to keep cattle enclosed.  It's a piece of art.  The design and artwork are well worth taking a look at.  One also has to remember this was originally the backside of the campus.  The main gate is on North Side.  And then let's not forget the history that took place here.  From students being sprayed with tear gas by then Governor Regan, the equal rights protests and the national guard with guns.

Next time you pass through the gate, stop and take a look at the design and artwork.  Then do a bit of historical research to learn what's happened in the shadow of the gate.  The world you live in today was greatly influenced by what happened here.< /text>< Pictures>

This shop is one of the best that I've ever visited and I've seen a lot of shops in my day (just trust me on that one). The owner, Dave, knows his stuff inside and out. < Text>
I've been a loyal client every month since 2013 (it has gone thru a few name changes since then lol), and I would NEVER go anywhere else.  Hands down, this is the best wax boutique in the county.  I think I first found them (then 'Wax in the City') on Yelp - and was very impressed by the reviews, so decided to check it out.  The boutique is so cute.  The girls are the sweetest, most friendly people - and I love my Angie!  This place is Clean, clean, clean!   The wax they use is top of the line, and they use different types of wax on different parts - so they obviously know what they're doing.  And in all the years I have been going, I have Never seen anyone Double Dip!  Don't cancel last minute/no-show - it'll cost you!  These girls rely on their appointments, and they fill up quickly... I think walk-ins might have a tough time, because this place is regularly booked solid (but that's what happens when you're the best).  Their booking website is really easy to use, and you can make any changes to your appointment.  Hey!  If you're a student, you can get a special discount on Thursdays - I love that!  I have never been to their downtown location - but Angie only works at Normal Heights, so that's where I go.  I hear it's really nice, though.
Go. Ask for Angie. You won't be disappointed.<//Text>

< text>
Upon arriving in the area, the parking is across the street but limited in spaces. If needed, there is some street/neighborhood parking. Staff was accommodating for my large party of seven + one dog. We didn't wait too long for a table luckily and we're immediately seated away from other tables per Covid-19 precautions. Our server Hector was very funny and gave great suggestions of what to order. He served us to the best of his abilities and was wearing a mask as well as gloves to make sure we were comfortable dining here. I was not disappointed with each dish ordered from what Hector suggested. The eggs benevilla, the eggs Nouveau, the peanut butter bacon banana bacon french toast sandwich and the beignets were delicious. I hope to be back when I'm in the area again.</text>

CN has put in very thoughtful measures - masks, gloves for the wait staff; the process of only certain staff will clear the used plates and flatware; the way to pay bills. < text>
We shared an order of bacon maple beignets
They were absolutely decadent! Lots of bacon crumbles, a good amount of maple syrup

I ordered the bacon, gorgonzola & caramelized onion frittata
It comes topped with diced tomatoes and arugula

The bacon flavor was more subtle than I'd prefer, the tomatoes and arugula added a nice, refreshing layer to the profile

My youngest daughter had chocolate brioche French toast
Pure decadence: a mountain of bananas, strawberries, and whipped cream, atop two slices of midnight dark French toast, a generous helping of nutella between them

Amazing flavor

My oldest daughter had the peanut butter, bacon, banana French toast sandwich
Two slices of Texas toast sized bread surrounded a dazzling mixture of PB, bacon, and bananas, and is served with a thick maple sauce

Incredible flavor

My dish came with a cornbread blueberry muffin
Different, but tasty, warmed, with butter

The check came with three miniature lemon poppy seed muffins with frosting and sprinkles
A delicious end to a great meal</text>

<Date>1571590632357< /Date>< rate>
4<//rate>
<Review>This restaurant is literally built in a house. It's super charming and they definitely embrace the New Orleans vibe.
Our group had a variety of things; The s'mores pancakes - SUPER sweet so I'd recommend splitting then unless you want to experience a huge sugar crash. The Poblano Del Mar - delicious but it's a lot for one person to take down - The rice was well seasoned, the pepper was well-cooked and wasn't mushy and the seafood and veggies meshed well with the entire dish. The one dish that was a little lackluster were the chocolate waffles - instead of having the chocolate chips mixed into the batter, they were out on top and therefore ended up burnt. So the waffle was really a plain waffle with burnt chocolate pieces, which was... Not great and went unfinished.

Overall though, yummy food, great service and a pretty short wait considering how busy it is.< /Review><pics>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipO0Rs9w2nubXuIf58BpWUotplfYVOPxufdQkTiA=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipME9nlju1v1nzLXzutS1LdtZrK3BKEAgQrJ9xfA=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]<//pics><Resp>None< /Resp><GmapID>0x80e9ace1d769e3e1:0x430ae333e970d2d4</GmapID></record>

<text>Restaurant is located in an old house.  Seating is available both inside and out.  The atmosphere is quite nice.  The staff were very pleasant with warm smiles.  The breakfast menu is very extensive with selections of American and Mexican classics.  They have a very large pancake selection with various fruits and syrups available, eggs Benedict, waffles, etc.  They have Saratoga sparkling water available which is nice.  Visited here just after opening during the week.  I would imagine this place would get rather crowded on the weekends.  Two eggs and two strips of bacon were $5 and then pancakes were about $10.  I ordered the blueberry pancakes and there were plenty of blueberries. I saw some reviews mentioning dogs but I didn't see any during my visit. Recommended.</text>< rating>

I found this place via a search for an "organic breakfast in Ventura." The atmosphere was great, the service rocked, the flavor profile was a great attempt.  But the more I eat fresh, locally grown organic food the more I can taste the substandard subtleties of conventionally farmed ingredients. There is a flatness to it. So my hope would be that they find local farmers and get better ingredients...because really amazing food starts there.<//review>

< text>
Great atmosphere on the outside patio, surrounded by trees. Wait staff was fabulous as was the food. Relaxed brunch with family and even had the dog with us since we were outside.

<Text>The wait time was about 20 minutes. We were sat in a weird and busy zone inside the house, between the bathroom and what we're guessing was a kitchen, which had waiters constantly going in and out. It just felt really busy around us.

The food was good but really rich. We felt full after our starter alone - the maple bacon beignets. I ordered the matcha green tea tiramisu pancakes. It was tasty and fluffy but too much for me to eat at one sitting. I also ordered a side of bacon (my fave) which was probably the saltiest bacon I've ever had. I didn't like the bacon on its own but thought maybe they went for a saltier option for the maple bacon beignets, to offset the sugary sweetness of that item, one of the most popular items on their menu< /Text>< Pics>

< user>
107556626683689474498<//user>
< name>
Sharon Gorsch<//name>
<Date>1531588092286< /Date><Rate>5< /Rate>< Text>
This local gem affords a fun atmosphere with its colorful interior which dons eclectic furnishings reminiscent of Victorian, art deco & 50's diner eras. It's not a surprise there is a waiting list for a table because locals and visitors experience a culinary delight with any menu choice. Today hubby and I started with beignets, which were melt in your mouth amazing! Our main courses of sausage frittata and Nouveau garden omlet with au gratin potatoes were abundant servings of pleasurable flavor. We've been coming here for years and have always enjoyed delicious food, friendly, prompt and attentive service. We immediately think of Cafe Nouveau when hosting out of town visitors. Bon appetite!</Text>

<Time>1508330443530< /Time>< Review>
Charming breakfast place in a converted old home. Delicious Breakfast Benedicts for around $12. Complimentary coffee, cider and fruited water while you wait for a table. And tiny complimentary cupcakes are served in place of after dinner mints! Wanted to try the Beignets...but was too full. Highly recommend the au gratin breakfast potatoes. Sadly, no Diet Coke...my only disappointment. Tattooed be host was delightful. Server could have been friendlier but excellent bus staff kept our glasses filled and was very attentive!< /Review>
